main event: A civilian reported observing twelve lights arranged in a horizontal line in the sky over Chicago, Illinois on June 7, 1966.
interesting points: The lights blinked on and off consecutively from one end to the other., The object was traveling at an altitude of approximately 500 - 800 feet., The observer noted the object changing its course from west to south, then east, and finally north., The observation lasted for about 10 minutes., The report concluded with a possible identification as an aircraft.
sighted object: twelve blinking lights in the sky
